attr.title: Phillip's Seafood Express
attr.caption: Phillips seafood tradition started a century ago on Hoopers Island, where the A.E. Phillips & Son processing plant sourced wild crabs, fish and oysters in season from the Chesapeake Bay. In those early days, the fresh seafood traveled by steamship daily to Baltimore, where it was bound for local restaurants and fishmongers. Over the past 100 years, we have grown our company by leaps and bounds by holding fast to these simple principles: serve classic seafood favorites, provide outstanding service, and create a memorable dining experience for our guests.

attr.title: The Club BWI
attr.caption: The Club at BWI, shared-use lounge, is an ‘inclusive’ lounge open to all passengers regardless of airline, class of ticket, Frequent Flyer status, or affinity program participation. In addition to providing a lounge solution for today’s traveler, the shared-use lounge satisfies the needs of multiple airlines. The Club BWI offers this for all travelers at a price of $40.
